						<summary>

						<p>Damaged and partly built in. Refers to the redemption of some mortgage by payment of 52 <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> and seems to record a gift of paddy by Tīraṉ Paramēśvaraṉ of ••• ••• •••• puṟam in Malaimaṇḍalam probably for supply of <hi rend="italic">Śeṅgaḻunīr</hi> garlands. Also mentions the <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> village Tiruttaṅgāval and refers to a transanction made during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Māṟavarmaṉ Sundarapāṇḍya (I).</hi> Rājēndra of the record is evidently <hi rend="bold">Rājēndra III.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
